III

A POSSIBLE SOURCE OF ‘AETNA’

THE pseudo-Aristotelian treatise Περὶ Κόσμου has many points in common with our poem. It is a little work, only twenty-eight octavo pages in Bekker's Oxford edition of 1837 3 for this very reason the resemblances are more striking. They have not, so far as I know, been noticed by any one hitherto. They are of two kinds, (Ι) general, (2) particular.

Ι. α. Both the Περὶ Κόσμου and the poem exhibit the same enthusiasm for seientific research and the investigation of natural phenomena.
